description: The 'plugins' dataset provides comprehensive information about various plugins, including their development status, identification, and usage metrics. Each entry in the dataset represents a plugin, detailing whether it is in development (isDev), its unique identifier (id), and a descriptive label. The dataset also includes a detailed description of each plugin's functionality, which can range from geospatial analysis to text preparation and cloud vision tasks. Additionally, the dataset records the author or authors responsible for each plugin, offering insight into the creators behind these tools. Tags associated with each plugin provide a quick reference to its thematic or functional categories, such as 'NLP' or 'Geospatial'. The version column indicates the current version of the plugin, while project_usages and total_usages columns provide data on how frequently and in which projects the plugins are utilized. This dataset is particularly useful for developers and data scientists looking to understand the landscape of available plugins, their applications, and their popularity within different projects.
shortDesc: Dataset of plugins with details on development, usage, and authorship.

columns.name: isDev
columns.comment: Indicates if the plugin is in development.

columns.name: author
columns.comment: Creator or creators of the plugin.

columns.name: project_usages
columns.comment: Projects where the plugin is used.

columns.name: total_usages
columns.comment: Number of times the plugin is used.
